to achieve a goal.

2
00:00:13,340 --> 00:00:17,060
Another way they can experience stress is through conflict.

3
00:00:17,060 --> 00:00:22,170
Conflict occurs when two or more incompatible motivations compete for expression.

4
00:00:22,170 --> 00:00:26,660
A lot of work has being done on work-life balance and how that can produce stress and

5
00:00:26,660 --> 00:00:27,660
conflict.

6
00:00:27,660 --> 00:00:32,480
There are demands of family life, and the demands of our working lives compete with

7
00:00:32,479 --> 00:00:33,480
that.

8
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:39,190
Sometimes, both family and work need attention at the same time, so it becomes very difficult

9
00:00:39,190 --> 00:00:42,060
for people to try to satisfy both sets of demands.

10
00:00:42,060 --> 00:00:43,790
Oftentimes, they can’t.

11
00:00:43,790 --> 00:00:50,940
There are actually three different types of conflict: The approach-approach, the avoidance-avoidance,

12
00:00:50,940 --> 00:00:51,940
and the approach-avoidance.

13
00:00:51,940 --> 00:00:56,850
We’ll go through some examples to illustrate them.

14
00:00:56,850 --> 00:01:00,430
The first type is what we call approach-approach type conflict.

15
00:01:00,430 --> 00:01:04,299
Now all of these conflict types are not equally stressful.

16
00:01:04,299 --> 00:01:09,079
The approach-approach type conflict is where you have to choose between two positive alternatives.

17
00:01:09,079 --> 00:01:11,350
You’ve got two competing goals.

18
00:01:11,350 --> 00:01:16,350
I know all of you are not necessarily going to go into Psychology as a career, but for

19
00:01:16,350 --> 00:01:21,090
the sake of this example, imagine that your goal is to become a Psychologist.

20
00:01:21,090 --> 00:01:24,990
When you finish your study, you start applying for jobs and you get a letter of offer from

21
00:01:24,990 --> 00:01:28,250
one place which just so happens to be a ski resort.

22
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:30,960
They’ve been looking for a psychologist.

23
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:35,590
If you accept that job, what you’ll be doing is talking to people, giving them some motivational

24
00:01:35,590 --> 00:01:40,220
encouragement about their skiing on the slope, to try more difficult runs and things like

25
00:01:40,220 --> 00:01:45,460
that, and helping them deal with the disappointment of falling over when they ski.

26
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:48,920
That won’t take much of your time, so you can have a lot of time to sit in front of

27
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:53,270
the fireplace and drink hot chocolates and go skiing yourself as well, and they’ll

28
00:01:53,270 --> 00:01:54,542
pay you lots of money to do that.

29
00:01:54,542 --> 00:01:59,310
There are no jobs like this in psychology, but imagine if there is one.

30
00:01:59,310 --> 00:02:03,159
You’re pretty excited by the possibility of a career on the snow.

31
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:05,990
But, you receive another letter of offer the next day.

32
00:02:05,990 --> 00:02:10,679
It is from a very exclusive island resort and they want you to run some mindfulness

33
00:02:10,679 --> 00:02:13,900
sessions for the clients who are paying a lot of money.

34
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:17,870
You only really have to do a couple of those sessions a day, so you’ve got a lot of time

35
00:02:17,870 --> 00:02:20,980
to sit on the beach, drink daiquiris, and chill out.

36
00:02:20,980 --> 00:02:23,459
They’ll give you lots of money as well.

37
00:02:23,459 --> 00:02:27,000
You’ve got to choose between these two jobs.

38
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,650
Which one do you choose?

39
00:02:28,650 --> 00:02:30,209
Is that a hard choice?

40
00:02:30,209 --> 00:02:34,889
Yes, it is, so it could produce stress.

41
00:02:34,889 --> 00:02:37,260
Why is that stressful?

42
00:02:37,260 --> 00:02:39,980
You know they are likely to both have VERY positive outcomes.

43
00:02:39,980 --> 00:02:44,209
By choosing one, you lose the positive aspects of the other one.

44
00:02:44,209 --> 00:02:47,559
Also, you don’t know which option would be better.

45
00:02:47,559 --> 00:02:51,579
One of them might be slightly more positive than the other, but it’s really hard to

46
00:02:51,579 --> 00:02:52,790
tell.

47
00:02:52,790 --> 00:02:56,430
This is stressful because you’re giving up the positive aspects of the one you didn’t

48
00:02:56,430 --> 00:02:57,430
choose.

49
00:02:57,430 --> 00:03:00,529
And this is what causes the stress.

50
00:03:00,529 --> 00:03:03,169
What if the conflict is slightly different?

51
00:03:03,169 --> 00:03:08,109
The second type is what we call avoidance-avoidance type conflict, where we have to choose between

52
00:03:08,109 --> 00:03:11,559
